;
; BIND Zone Template for Dynamic DNS
; =============================================================================
; This is a template file used by dyndnsupdate.sh to generate zone files.
; 
; CONFIGURATION:
;   Replace the following placeholders with your actual values:
;   - HOST.COM    -> Your actual domain name (e.g., example.com)
;   - SERVERIP    -> Your DNS server's static IP address
;   - admin       -> Your admin email (dots become @ in DNS notation)
;
; PLACEHOLDERS:
;   - HOMEREPLACEME -> Automatically replaced by dyndnsupdate.sh with your
;                      home's current external IP address
;
; USAGE:
;   Do not edit this file directly for IP updates. The dyndnsupdate.sh script
;   copies this template, substitutes the IP, and creates the final zone file.
;
; Last Updated: 2026
; =============================================================================

$TTL    604800
@       IN      SOA     ns1.HOST.COM. admin.HOST.COM. (
                        2026010301      ; Serial (YYYYMMDDNN format, increment on changes)
                         604800         ; Refresh (7 days)
                          86400         ; Retry (1 day)
                        2419200         ; Expire (28 days)
                         604800 )       ; Negative Cache TTL (7 days)
;

; -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Name Server Records
; -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; NS record pointing to your authoritative name server
HOST.COM.       IN      NS      ns1.HOST.COM.

; -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; A Records for Name Server
; -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; The IP address of your name server itself
HOST            IN      A       SERVERIP

; -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; A Records for Domain
; -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Root domain (example.com)
@               IN      A       SERVERIP

; www subdomain (www.example.com)
www             IN      A       SERVERIP

; Dynamic home subdomain (home.example.com)
; This IP is automatically updated by dyndnsupdate.sh
home            IN      A       HOMEREPLACEME
